In its current state, I cannot recommend this game because it has one glaring flaw. It's not a bad game fundamentally, I actually felt quite compelled to keep climbing whenever I fell because unlike Getting Over It, the controls aren't complete horseshit. There were times where I thought the colliders were a bit bullshit and the character didn't grab a ledge when he should've or something, but that's whatever in the grand scheme of things, you just climb back up and get better at it. The issue here is that the game doesn't fucking save.

The level is huge. I feel like I got pretty damn high in my time playing, but based on what I've seen from other people playing, I probably got maybe 1/3rd in my best run, which took about 2 or 3 hours? It's absurd how high this game goes (and thus how much progress you can potentially lose), which would be a fantastic thing to know that I'm getting so much content out of my purchase, but combined with the lack of saving, I have zero motivation to keep playing this game at the moment.

You missed a jump and lost 2 hours of progress? Fine, start climbing back up, that's the point of a game like this.
Your game crashed, which happened to me twice? Fuck you, I guess. 
You've made a lot of progress but want to take a break and maybe play some other games for a bit? Fuck you, you have to finish the entire thing in one sitting.
You want to eat, handle a real world emergency, go to sleep, etc? Enjoy leaving your computer on all day and pray that the game doesn't crash while you're away, which even if it doesn't and you go back to playing it, you're just back to "you can't do anything else until you beat it."

I really don't understand why this is a feature. I looked it up and there's actually a post from the developers about it that says, "We understand that some resent the lack of opportunities to save progress, but the concept of the game is not to 'save game' - the point is that each successive level raises the stakes in the game, and the danger of falling down would be more significant." Saving progress is not the same thing as a checkpoint. I fail to see how saving progress would make the jumps any less dangerous, you just save the falls as well. People don't resent the lack of saving because we want an easy mode, it's because we want to be able to actually play the game without having to dedicate an entire fucking day to this game where we may or may not even beat it. Even Getting Over It saves your progress. If they ever add saving I might come back to this game and change the review, otherwise I doubt I'll ever touch it again.

Normally when playing a game like this, the frustration comes from losing progress. Instead, I found myself frustrated with the abysmal text-to-speech narration, clearly attempting to emulate Bennett Foddy in writing but coming nowhere close, the clunky physics engine that was either not intended for a game of this style or not tested anywhere near as thoroughly as it should've been, and the absolutely shallow visual design and "art" throughout. Awkward invisible walls in areas seem completely inappropriate for a game in this genre and level design choices also send mixed messages, with some openly stating that they want you to find your path to the top on your own and then others having arrows pointing you in the exact direction you need to go. Overall, this game is unfinished at best and a lazy cash grab with shitty adverts at worst. You'd do better to just play a Roblox obby or something, to be completely honest.

Only Up! is an interesting title. I have a bit of patience, and as a streamer I do enjoy games that are fun when I fail at them. The platforming isn't bad, and it does what it sets out to do well. I have not played Getting Over It, but from my understanding this is essentially a very similar 3D platforming version of that, though the "philosophical" aspect of it is genuinely laughter inducing. The translation is bad, and truly I wish I could just mute the main character.

I would give this game a positive review based on gameplay alone, however one thing that should be noted is that this game advertises Goblintown NFTs very heavily. It uses the art, along with what must be other AI generated assets. The main character wears Goblintown merch, and the art is plastered in bizarre places throughout the game. I did not entirely know this until after my time spend playing the game.

As such, due to its use of Goblintown assets, I cannot recommend you spend money on this title.

First off, this game is a fun challenge. However, the devs have soft egos. I understand patching glitches that void the game, such as double jumping on a certain place to get you to the end. However the devs patched a couple of parts of the game that allowed players a fun speed run, all to force players into one of the harsher and more punishing areas of the game for the sake of it. Don't get me wrong, this game is fun in its own right, but by the devs fixing certain aspects and forcing players to play it their way is a salty response to it. Instead of saying "wow, that was creative", the devs said "wow that looks like fun, lets remove it". Its sad and at least getting over it kept the speed run tactics in the game, allowing players to experience the game in whatever way they choose. Not throwing a tantrum and removing them. All youtube videos from today onwards are invalidated starting from (around) the cannon. so enjoy I guess

After 11 hours, I have finished this interesting game, which leaves me angry, laughing, hitting the wall, hitting the keyboard, but above all, even if it is strange, "Fun".

It's a game that if you don't have patience you don't have a chance to finish it, you will fall thousands of times "What happened to me", but still I continued, being angry and almost throwing in the towel "Something I never do" and finally reached the goal.

It is true that it has bugs, for example:

-Delay in recognizing the jumps.
-Delay when recognizing that you hold on to objects.
-At times you jumped on an obstacle and you went under the object and ended up at the beginning "Which frustrates a lot."

The positive:

-Good soundtrack "Little, but there was".
-Good graphics.
-Spectacular amount of levels and each one different "Obviously".
-Virtually the whole game, very well detailed.

Important note:

-Do not get carried away by negative reviews, from people who for the sole reason that they are not able to advance or finish it, because it is already a bad game and it is not like that. Give it a chance you won't regret it.

And something else "It does not have Check-Points, nor manual saving", so if you want to finish it, you will have to play continuously or leave your pc on for good hours while you sleep and then continue.

Rating 9/10 (-1 point for certain bugs)

POV: Average Mountain climber

The game on its own is fun but not very long. In the beginning I was a bit annoyed that you could not close the game and continuing from the same spot later (like in “getting over it”, you can’t reload an older save file to correct mistakes but you can close the game and continuing from the same spot) but the game is so short and simple that it doesn’t rly matter. After about 4 I completed the game. The game does not rly have a lot of replay value. I tried to speedrun it a couple of times, and I guess it is a cool game if you are into speed running because there are a lot of creative and risky ways to optimize your route, but otherwise there is not rly any reason to open the game again after you completed it the first time. I have only encountered a couple of bugs right in the starting area.

If you like games where you have to play the whole game in one season and where you get punished hard for mistakes, then this game is quit fun. Only Up - 
As you look at the name "Only Up" you would think that there is only one way which would be up, but no. The amount of physical and mental pain that this game has caused me could not be fixed by the worlds greatest doctor or the worlds best therapists. I thought "Getting Over It with Bennet Foddy" was the only game that could cause this amount of pain, but some how "Only Up" has drastically beat "Getting Over It". Oh but dont forget if you want to take a quick break from the extreme torture and play something else.. weeellll you cant, unless you want to restart from the very beginning.

What is Only Up - (SPOILERS)
When you start the game "Only Up" you play as some random little kid that for some reason decides to climb buildings, pipes, roads, cars, and even more random objects that just make it harder for you to succeed in your goal of reaching the end. Around half way through the game you get to a point where you think you beat the game and you're filled with joy, but as you find out...its not the end. Towards the end of the game you make it to a maze with a dragon that at first you would think that it spooks you and just flies away, no. During that whole part of the game that dragon is the root of all evil, its your worst enemy, its-its... its just more pain that the game causes. When you finish the game its somewhat rewarding as you realize that through and the pain and suffering you push through to the very end to accomplish your goal

First things first please ignore the trolls complaining about NFT shilling, the game never asks you to purchase ANYTHING nor does it direct you to any NFT marketplace, it's simply background art and you wouldn't know it was an NFT if someone didn't tell you.  

 This game is a trial a tribulation of skill jumps, well timed ledge grabs and lots of frustration. It will piss you off endlessly, it will make you quit and it will make you question why even bother. That's what makes it so special, it's not just a game made for streamers or content creators. It has a subtle story of someones life told through a reoccurring AI voice, it's there if you're patient and make your way up. It might seem like someone just bought the entire Unreal asset marketplace and needed to make their money back but it has a lot more going for it. 

  There are some really well thought out level design here, from spooky black and white old time horror to a more psychedelic space vibe. Typically there are multiple ways to traverse the level, others there's only one way with hidden obstacles or break away floors. It challenges you but at the same time rewards your progression with getting to see what lies further above. Did you finally make it to the end or is that another platforming nightmare above. 

  Please don't listen to nay sayers about bad optimization or NFT ads, this game is made with care and love. Good Luck and see you at the top!

Only up..? Im going only down..

Only Up is an exhilarating game that pushes the boundaries of climbing challenges. Its unique concept instantly grabbed my attention as a fan of games like "Getting Over It" and "Jump King." The visually janky level design adds a quirky and captivating atmosphere, giving the game its own distinct identity.

What sets Only Up apart are its intuitive controls. Unlike other challenging games, the controls are easy to grasp, allowing you to focus on the climbing mechanics and the thrilling adventure. The developers struck a perfect balance, making the controls responsive and precise, enhancing the climbing experience.

Like other Foddian games, Only Up breaks away from traditional mechanics by not relying on extrinsic rewards. Instead, the joy comes from the simple act of climbing higher. This refreshing approach adds purity and immersion, making each conquered climb a truly satisfying accomplishment. With its climbing-focused mechanics, accessible controls, and visually janky design, Only Up stands out among similar games, keeping players engaged from start to finish.

I would recommend Only Up to fans of challenging platformers and climbing adventures. Its unique blend of accessible controls, captivating visuals, and the thrill of ascending higher provides an unmatched sense of accomplishment. Prepare for an unforgettable climbing journey that tests your skills and leaves you wanting more. Just be prepared to fall, and fall, and fall... until finally you make it to the top.

まず第一に「全著作権所有」って表記がタイトル画面にあるが、フリー素材使ってそうなんで、その時点で著作権的にアウトなゲーム。人におススメしない方が良いです。

ゲームの内容ですが、「画面でキャラクターが動くだけで面白い」と感じる人にはいかもです。
また「上れたことへの達成感がある」らしいですが、それに関しては慎重にプレイすればどうとでもなりそうなので感じる人は感じてて下さい。
昨今のゲームに基本ある「爽快感」や「ゲーム性」は一切ありません。判定のガバガバさや、物理エンジンのバグを「ゲーム性」と称するなら話は別ですが。
言ってしまえば初めてゲームを作成する学生が作った大作。ゲームの根幹である基本システムを適当に作って量だけを増やした作品。

ゲームの世界観は特にありません。
各言語の応援メッセージが流れる看板があると思えば、宇宙服には韓国の国旗が設定言語に関係なく描かれてますし、時々話しかけてくる女性の声や、背景オブジェ（落ちている新聞や壁の落書き）は英語。
地上には特に意味もなく突っ立ってる人オブジェ。何かを指さしているが、指さす先には何もない。
サッカーボールを３つ持って遊ぶ少年少女。（ボールのサイズがすべて違う。）
「ああ、フリー素材を持ってきて無理やりサイズを合わせたんだろうな～」という感想。
「何やってるんだこいつ」っていう頭がおかしい人を見たような初見の面白さはあるかもしれませんね。

二度とプレイしません。メモリももったいないのでアンインストール推奨です。

FUN GAME

Needs patience. Easy controls. High repeatability. Great for speed-running even without executing tough glitches. Very interesting game design. Slightly linear is some parts, but room for some area exploration. Lot of pop culture/ mythological references to explore too. Looks decent even in lower graphics settings. Some weird grim commentary and annoying music. I play with the sound off. 

Recommend lowering mouse sensitivity to 60-70% (will need experimentation as DPI and comfort levels vary). Lock frame rate to 60/90, and lowering draw distance to Medium if frame issues appear. 

Slightly jank behaviour in some parts, for example falling into small crevices will result in character getting stuck with no reset button. 

Still a lot of fun. Do give it a shot. I give it 3.5 floating cars out of 5. (will change to 4 if the annoying AI lady voice stops talking or if a reset button for glitches are introduced)

Today when I walked into my economics class I saw something I dread every time I close my eyes. Someone had brought their new gaming laptop to class. The Forklift he used to bring it was still running idle at the back. I started sweating as I sat down and gazed over at the 700lb beast that was his laptop. He had already reinforced his desk with steel support beams and was in the process of finding an outlet for a power cable thicker than Amy Schumer's thigh. I start shaking. I keep telling myself I'm going to be alright and that there's nothing to worry about. He somehow finds a fucking outlet. Tears are running down my cheeks as I send my last texts to my family saying I love them. The teacher starts the lecture, and the student turns his laptop on. The colored lights on his RGB Backlit keyboard flare to life like a nuclear flash, and a deep humming fills my ears and shakes my very soul. The entire city power grid goes dark. The classroom begins to shake as the massive fans begin to spin. In mere seconds my world has gone from vibrant life, to a dark, earth shattering void where my body is getting torn apart by the 150mph gale force winds and the 500 decibel groan of the cooling fans. As my body finally surrenders, I weep, as my school and my city go under. I fucking hate gaming laptops.

The game is simple, fun, and frustrating. My biggest issue is the invisible walls that you run into that drop you all the way to the ground. A completely clear and open area to jump to and you hit the wall like *spoiler* Hemsworth in Cabin in the Woods *end spoiler*. I've done that multiple times now and fallen all the way back down. Other than that the game is entertaining and I got it for $7. To me it's worth $7 for a few hours of entertainment.

"Only Up!" is a masterpiece that demands infinite patience and a frustration tolerance of cosmic proportions. If you're even remotely fond of enjoying your life, brace yourself, because this game will make you want to move to a remote island.

The game is deceptively simple. You take control of Jackie, a moderately athletic yet perpetually gloomy child with dreams of escaping poverty. And guess what? You're the chosen one to accompany Jackie on this wild ride. But here's the kicker—this game is specifically engineered to push you to your limits. It will have you questioning everything, from your sanity to your life choices. Your keyboard will tremble with fear every time you launch "Only Up!" because it knows it's about to face a relentless barrage of keystrokes that would make a concert pianist's fingers weep.

If you happen to be a gamer with divorced parents, "Only Up!" should come with a warning label. It will unlock the deepest recesses of your childhood trauma and evoke memories of that time when your parents couldn't agree on whose turn it was to pick you up from school. Prepare to confront emotional baggage you didn't even know you had.

I'd proudly give it a 10/10 recommendation for those masochistic souls who thrive on digital punishment and have an exceptional sense of humor. After all, what better way to cope with life's absurdities than to subject yourself to the virtual equivalent?

May the force be with you, and never again.

이 게임에서는 플랫폼을 "Cling" 즉 "매달리기"를 통해 붙잡고 올라갈 수 있다는 장점이 있는데요.
이를 통해 많은 플레이어들이 좌절감에서 벗어나 소위 "할 만하다"고 생각하는 것 같아 진입장벽이 낮다고 여기는 것 같습니다.
하지만 이것만 믿고 들어가서는 안 될 게임임에는 틀림없습니다.
이 게임은 3D 플랫포머에서 기본적으로 지켜지고 있는 문법들이 지켜지지 않고 있다는 점에서 몹시 배신감을 느끼게 만드는 게임입니다.

배신감을 느꼈던 부분은 크게 3가지였습니다.

1. 가속 후 관성 판정
점프 시 Shift를 누르며 대시하며 점프할 수도 있고 그냥 점프할 수도 있죠.
대시하면서 점프를 하면 가속이 붙게 되는 건 이치적입니다.
그리고 그것 때문에 관성이 붙어서 미끄러운 판정이 생기는 것도 이치적이에요.
하지만 이 게임에서는 관성값이 고정값이어서 대시를 아주 약간만 이용해도 엄청난 거리를 미끄러지게 됩니다.

2. 도움 닫기 판정
플랫폼에 서서 도움닫기를 하지 못하면 앞으로 가면서 점프를 할 수가 없습니다.
이게 무슨 소리냐 하면, 캐릭터 앞에 1픽셀이라도 플랫폼이 남아있지 않으면 전진 키를 누르면서 점프를 할 경우 그냥 뚝 떨어지기만 할 뿐, 점프를 누를 수가 없다는 소리예요.
왜냐하면 전진을 하는 순간 1픽셀 앞은 허공이 되고, 허공에서는 점프를 할 수가 없으니까요.
이 부분이 많은 3D 플랫포머 게임과 다른 부분이죠.
더블 점프가 불가능한 게임들에서도 체공 시간 개념을 만들거나 캐릭터의 판정 크기를 수정해서 플랫폼에 약간 걸쳐 있을 수 있게끔 설계해서 어떻게든 점프를 할 수 있게 만드는 게 일반적이란 말이죠?
그런데 이 게임은 그딴 거 없습니다.
왜 이렇게까지 이 부분에 대해 열정적으로 논하게 되냐하면, 이것이 굉장히 자주 일어나는 일이기 때문이에요.
앞서 언급한 매달리기 직후의 상황에서 이런 일이 발생하게 되는데요.
매달려서 올라온 다음에 바로 뒤 돌아서 앞으로 가면서 점프하게 되면 이런 일이 발생하게 됩니다.
그러면 나는 분명 점프를 눌렀는데 점프가 안 눌린 것처럼 판정이 나오기 때문에 허무하게 그냥 밑으로 떨어지는 거죠.
그때의 배신감이란...

3. 낙하 시의 XY축 이동속도 문제
이 문제는 정말 악질이라고밖에 말할 수 없는데...
다른 게임 대비 캐릭터의 이동속도에 비해 낙하할 때의 XY축 이동속도가 터무니없이 느리다는 게 제 생각입니다.
거의 조작이 안 먹힐 정도로 캐릭터가 미동도 하지 않죠.
그래서 한 번 낙하하기 시작하면 그냥 거의 손 놓고 바라만 보게 되고, 무력감에 빠지게 됩니다.
이 게임의 특징이 맵이 Z축으로 엄청나게 높다는 것인데, 그래서 낙하도 엄청 오래 하게 되잖아요?
낙하하면서 어떻게든 살아보겠다고 아둥바둥 컨트롤 해보겠다고 키보드 두드려보면 뭣도 안 됩니다.
그게 사람을 미치게 하죠.

위에서 언급하는 3가지 점들은 일반적인 3D 플랫포머에서 생각되는 것들과 좀 많이 다릅니다.
저는 이 점들이 이 게임의 특장점이 된다기보다
이 게임의 단점이 된다고 생각하기 때문에 이 게임을 비추천하는 바이고,
이 게임에 시간을 쓰기보다는 다른 좋은 게임들이 많이 나와 있기 때문에
그런 게임들을 사서 하는 편이 건강에 더 좋다고 생각합니다.

This game has it's flaws, but those flaws matter little for how this game is supposed to be played. 

If you are buying this game because you watched your favorite streamer play it, then you should already know how the game plays. It is designed to be difficult and annoying, but also deeply satisfying when you break your previous record. For me, this game is A LOT more enjoying than Jump King. 

I play this game every weekend with my friends and we take turns passing the controller on the couch and seeing who can get the highest. We make drinking games out of it, we don't take it seriously and we have a good time. Occasionally we hop on a discord call and use Keyboard and Mouse which is obviously easier than controller, but its really about having fun with good friends and NOT taking the game seriously.

For only being $9.99 the game is worth the price imo. If you are a loner with no one to play with, find a nobody streamer playing it and try to compete with them on either time or total height climbed, because this game gets old immediately if you just play alone and aren't the type to get intrinsic satisfaction for breaking your previous height.

Game with friends 10/10

Solo 5/10 unless you truly enjoy gaming alone and are looking for a mindless grind while you listen to music.

The idea behind the game is fun, but right now it's not in a place I can recommend it. 

After a few runs, I got to the icy part where some of the platforms drop, and when one of them started dropping it instantly teleported me to the beginning of the game, without giving me a chance to recover from the "fall". That's a [b] gamebreaking [/b] issue that needs fixing ASAP. 

The game is also lacking a checkpoint feature that's been requested by many. By "checkpoint" I mean something that allows you to quit the game and then come back to it wherever you left off. It could also help with the kind of bug that I experienced where not only was I back to the beginning, but trapped behind an invisible wall. 

Also, the settings are not persistent, and you have to config them every time you start the game up.

Happy to turn this into a positive review once they fix the above issues.

Getting Over It, Jump King, Pogostuck. All of these games are tightly designed, you might fall but it feels like your fault, the game is FUN to play, it might cause rage, but its fun. The best way to describe Only Up is a roblox obby that costs 10 dollars. It is not tightly designed, when i fall it feels like the fault of the buggy jumping mechanics. Half the time you don't know where to go. Also, no save system? Really? I just wanted to close the game to go make food and not have this game sucking up a ton of computing power since its not optimized either and now I gotta start all over again. Maybe I'll update my review once I actually beat it but I don't know. Its *fine* for youtuber content, but unlike the earlier examples i gave, its not fun to play alone.

I beat the game after over 21 hours of playing, and honestly it was a sense of rage-fun which really enlightened me. The music fits perfectly to the type of anger you feel after falling and hours worth of playtime, so it just kind of adds to that will to beat the game because you are mad at the game rather than at yourself. Though I admit that it does have a lot of bugs, they do come across as features (lol) and somewhat add to the aspect of what the game is intended to do and what it is made for. With my near entire day of playing this game I would recommend it as it has a sense of Getting Over It and your typical 3D platformer combined which is really a rare and exciting sight to see, especially in a game like this.

You know what this is. It's a rage game; a [Bennett] Foddy-like. If you are prone to taking such games super seriously, you may not enjoy it. At any time, a mistake could cost you a significant amount, if not all, of your progress. Personally, I am really enjoying it. Only Up has a significantly lower barrier to entry then its contemporaries. It's not like "Getting Over It" where a large portion of the difficulty is in the ridiculous control scheme. The controls in Only Up are tight and responsive. Give it a try if you like 3D platformers. I'll be coming back to finish this one the next time I have a few hours to spare.

Note: Apparently this game heavily advertises NFTs. Going in without knowing this, I didn't really notice it. The whole game is so surreal that anything just sorta fits in. Use common sense; NFTs are a scam.

Playing this game is like willingly slapping yourself in the face every once in a while. Been playing for a week or so, barely scratched the surface of this game. I keep falling. It sucks.
The worst part is that the game is really fun and addicting for me. Falling just makes me want to get the upper hand on the game when I try to go up again. It never works.
The game looks really nice and runs perfectly for me, though the music and the text to speech voice can be a bit annoying. I feel it's fair in its difficulty for the most part, it's a game about developing "muscle memory" in a way that somewhat mirrors Getting Over It. When you fall, it causes you to make changes in the way you approach the jump that you fell at. That keeps happening over and over until you can blast through parts of the game you were struggling with an hour prior.
Overall, I've been enjoying my time playing this, and will continue playing to try and get to the top. I'm not great at these types of games, but I enjoy the challenge and the feeling of making it to the top. I'd recommend this game for anyone who's into this sort of thing. It's very enjoyable once you get past the anguish of repeatedly falling.

First of all, great game, love it. It is a really difficult plattformer, but thats what i love about it. Hard challenges are, most of the time, good ones. Now i know almost 10 hours of playtime may not be that much, but i bought the game just yesterday after all. The highest point that i reached so far was the place thats completely made out of ice. Got there just a few minutes ago. However, because of a bug or glitch that made me go into a smaller plattform made of ice, somehow i ported instantly all the way down to the beginning. I was really frustrated of course. Which is my first negative point of critique, there are some bugs that really need to be fixed, or else they could ruin everything and multiple hours of playtime are basically down the drain. Second negative point of critique, save points. I know the game is meant to be long and hard and bringing the player to their limits, so honestly i am fine if there will never be checkpoints where you could teleport to or something, however, something it should really have is a save function when you leave the game and go to the main menu. Because honestly not everyone has the time or the nerves to play the game for multiple hours straight in order to just have a chance of finishing it. So at least spawning where you quit the game would be great, in order to not lose hours of playtime because you are taking a break or because you just wanna do something else. 
Another thing, the collectible items, like the crown or the brain or the heart, does someone know what they are for? Because i could not find anything about what they are for. Would be sad honestly if they are for nothing and do nothing at all. So if someone knows, please let me know. Other than that it would be worth a thought of adding save points there at these items. Just a suggestion though.
But anyways, great game, love it, but definitely still needs some improvements here and there in my opinion. Other than that i can recommend it if you like challenging plattformer.

If you enjoyed [i]Getting Over It[/i] for the challenge and journey through odd settings, consider checking this game out.

good game but any game without auto saves shouldn't be released. I am simply not going to sit down for 3 hours or more to beat this game, I have these things called "a job" and "friends" so that doesn't really work for me.  It's basically just saying "you can save our game but only if you have enough ram to keep it open". FUCK YOU. It would be so easy to have an option where you can toggle on and off auto save. I feel abusing save states would not be an issue, I have over 150 runs in getting over it and I have never found any way to abuse the save states in that game, the second you start to fall it saves and there is no way you can go back. I was excited to beat this game but unless I am willing to keep it running for weeks on end I feel like there is no feasible way for me to accomplish that. Buy but only if you are a sweaty loser who wants to play a game where all you do is walk and mantle for 5 hours straight holy shit. The development team must have been smoking percocet.

서론이 길었군요. 이 게임의 장단점을 이제부터 이야기 하겠습니다.
-장점-
1. 모든것을 이겨내고 끝냈을때의 게임 성취감은 다른 어떠한 게임에서 느끼지 못한 정복감과 성취감을 느낄수 있다.. (항아리 게임및 다른 명작게임보다 더한 성취감을 얹어줄듯?)
2. 게임 진행과정에서 주인공(우리의 고블린 옷을 입는 청소년)의 내레에션과 함께 온리업의 환경 변화가 참으로 이색적이고 참신하다. 정말 한편의 영화를 보는것 같기도 하고 정말 게임에서 내가 끝없는 세계 여행을 하는 느낌을준다. 정말 무슨 현실세계와 비현실세계, 천계, 천상계, 우주 등등 현실에서 사회에 치이고 힘들고 답답했던 분들에게 이 게임을 인내를 통해 도전해보는 걸 추천해본다. (정말 무슨 우리나라 명산들 예를 들어, 북한산, 설악산, 지리산, 한라산 등등 꼭대기에서 "야호"를 외치는 느낌을 받고 싶은분들께)
3. 우린 달려간다!!! 우린 승리한다!!!의 노래가 저절로 나오는 게임!!
4. 도전정신이 불타오르는 그들에게 과감히 추천을 해본다. 
5. 주말이나 휴일에 시간이 10시간? 이상 넉넉히 여유 있으신분들께 추천


-단점-
1. 항아리게임과의 비교? 흠... ㅋㅋ 2D와 3D의 차이를 여기서 느껴보길 바란다.
2. 중간에 게임저장? 그딴거 없다. 1트다.
3. 주변에 조심해야할 지인(여자친구나 어르신들)이 있을때 절대 하지마라 본인의 이미지 망친다.
4. 위와 마찬가지로 너가 하지 않았던 온갓 욕을 여기서 다 할수도 있다. 
5. 도데체 억까란 무엇인가? 이 게임을 통해 억까의 또 다른 정의를 내릴수 있다.
6. 하루에 2~3시간정도 여유로는 1트에 택도 없을것이다. 만약 성공했다면 그 사람은 정말 이 게임의 정말 달인이다.
7. 이 게임 엔딩을 못보고 끝낸다면 좀 많이 아쉬울것이다. 그러니 초반에 그냥 접던지... 계속 도전해라.
8. 억까도 심한데 중독성있다..

Generally I wouldn't bother writing reviews for bad games, but I feel like this game just has something that makes it that special. 
The mantling and jumping are difficult to master in the sense that the hitboxes of the subjects are badly designed and hard to see what you should be jumping onto. It feels extremely clunky. The animation of the mantling/walking/running also feel unpolished and seriously rough.
The text to speech narration feels like it's been auto generated and the music feels like it plays when you reach certain points, not when multiple events happen, which continues to make the game feel unfinished. 
As well as this, the game is terribly optimized, requiring me to turn all my settings (except for view distance, which I'd had to leave on Epic in order to see the rest of the map) to Low in order to even have a playable experience (100FPS barely) on a PC running 1440p, a 5800x3D, 3070Ti and 16GB of RAM.
Furthermore, the game will not save your progress if you exit to the main menu, this is just simply awful design and was the deciding factor of whether or not I would refund the game or not. 

Iverall, for the hour that I played this game, I was seriously disappointed. 
The game just feels like a bad, cheap 3D copy of Bennett Foddy's "Getting Over It" that's designed to attract attention for a week or two and make a quick dollar for the publisher. I will be refunding this game and will download it elsewhere to complete. 
It is absolutely not worth the 15NZD that it is being sold for. 
As well as this, I would've expected the game to be in an early-access stage, It is seriously unacceptable and outright disappointing for a game like this to be sold as a full release. 
Maybe with a few updates to improve hitboxes and animations, I could see the game actually being a fun and challenging platformer, but in it's current state, I would not recommend anyone to purchase this game, regardless if it goes on sale or not.

Overall score: 2/10

***SPOILER ALERT***SPOILER ALERT***SPOILER ALERT****First off, I went into this game looking for a challenge. I thought, hey, why not, a lot of people are playing lets give it a try. I struggled at first to get the mechanics down, granted I was using a controller mapped to the PC keys. I found my perfect sensitivity to go with my play style, before you know it we're conquering new heights no pun intended and our mental is strong from the small victories we had achieved, getting closer, and closer to the top this is where my mental was strongest. After scaling up for about 3 hours, I miss a jump to a blue truck and I am devastated, bewildered, my mental is breaking a little, I feel defeated. I get to the bottom, the beginning and hear a nice non trolling sound in my ears. Whomever decided to add that song in the game, I will forever be haunted by its cold embrace. So we pick ourselves back up, and are determined to get back to that truck, we scale back up after a few hours, I stare at the truck, it stares back, I make my jump again and fail, we scale back up i jump and fail, I'm losing my mind slowly by now and again I hear that sweet song of pain. I get back to the truck and I say "there's gotta be something I'm missing here" staring at the cold blue truck. I open my menu to gaze at the games controls and there it was in front of me this entire time, the word SPRINT!!!! I say, this has to be the way to make the jump, I muster up the courage and go for it, after so much misery and pain I finally made it across, I'm elated beyond belief!!!! I'm now well into my current run five or so hours in, we scale, and scale with the use of sprint and the slow motion godsend mechanic. We finally breach the clouds, and are now in the heavens, I move up with caution, and patience, breaching new heights as time passes. After about nine hours I get to the Mario Kart rainbow bridge, lets just say I return back to reality, I'm completely broken, i quit the game for the day, I'm lost, who even am I anymore, I go to sleep the nightmares begin. I wake up refreshed, watched a speed run to find all the skips up to the rainbow bridge, I complete a good amount making good time, I continue on, mental tested after my controller inverting somehow, and almsot getting Smaugged into oblivion if you know what I mean. I finally completed the game after a solid 139ish minutes, I feel like I have achieved a glorious final peace within. All-in-all this game was the most challenging gaming experience I've had, but also the most rewarding at the same time. I highly recommend the game to anyone looking for a great challenge like you've never experienced before, best of luck to you all. :)

Titel: Ein bezauberndes Abenteuer: Eine Bewertung von "Only Up!"

Bewertung: ★★★★☆ (4/5)

Rezension:

"Only Up!" ist ein faszinierendes und mitreißendes Spiel, das die Spieler auf ein zauberhaftes Abenteuer mitnimmt. Es bietet fesselnde Herausforderungen und lebendige visuelle Effekte. Obwohl ich meine Erfahrung mit Alzheimer für diese Rezension erfinde, kann ich Ihnen versichern, dass "Only Up!" ein unterhaltsames und immersives Erlebnis für Spieler aller Hintergründe bietet.

Die Handlung des Spiels dreht sich um eine Protagonistin namens Sarah, die sich auf eine phantastische Reise durch eine Reihe von Plattform-Levels begibt. Während ihr Gedächtnis verblassen mag, bleibt ihr Wille, sich zu erheben und jeden Level zu meistern, ungebrochen. Die Spielmechanik ist einfach, aber süchtig machend und ermöglicht es den Spielern, Sarah durch verschiedene Hindernisse zu steuern, Schätze zu sammeln und neue Level freizuschalten.

Eine der Stärken des Spiels liegt in seiner Fähigkeit, ein Gefühl von Staunen und Entdeckung zu erzeugen. Die lebendigen und farbenfrohen visuellen Effekte, gepaart mit fantasievollen Soundeffekten und einem bezaubernden Soundtrack, entführen die Spieler in eine fesselnde Welt. Jeder Level bietet einzigartige Herausforderungen und Überraschungen, die die Spieler begeistern und dazu anregen, weiter zu erkunden.

Trotz des spielerischen Charakters von "Only Up!" fügt die Einbeziehung von Alzheimer als thematisches Element eine zusätzliche Tiefe und Emotionalität hinzu. Während Sarah durch die Level aufsteigt, versagt ihr Gedächtnis zeitweise, was zu Momenten der Verwirrung und Orientierungslosigkeit führt. Diese Momente erinnern die Spieler an die Herausforderungen, denen Menschen mit Alzheimer gegenüberstehen, und fördern Empathie und Verständnis.

Die Spielmechanik spiegelt auf geschickte Weise die kognitiven Schwankungen wider, die Menschen mit Alzheimer erleben. Gelegentlich können die Spieler auf veränderte Spielmechaniken oder verzerrte visuelle Effekte stoßen, die Sarahs Perspektive widerspiegeln, während sie sich in ihrer sich verändernden Welt zurechtfindet. Dieser einzigartige Ansatz verleiht nicht nur dem Gameplay eine interessante Note, sondern fördert auch ein tieferes Verständnis für die Erfahrungen von Menschen mit Alzheimer.

"Only Up!" ist ein wunderbares Spiel, das mit seinem fesselnden Gameplay und seiner einfallsreichen Handlung begeistert. Es bietet sowohl Unterhaltung als auch eine Gelegenheit, sich mit dem Thema Alzheimer auseinanderzusetzen. Tauchen Sie ein in diese zauberhafte Welt und erleben Sie die Freude des Aufstiegs, während Sie Sarah auf ihrem Abenteuer begleiten.

The game as a platformer is doing its job okay'ish. However, as many already said, the game lacks some proper QoL features such as checkpoints, especially since getting back up is so tedious thanks to slow climbing animations and poorly implemented music/voicelines.

While you climb the random stock asset tower parkour, you're constantly being bothered by a cheap AI voice that keeps bragging about how bad life in Favela is and how abusive the family of the narrator is etc. Nobody cares. It doesn't sound interesting and because it keeps repeating itself over and over again as you repeat the parkour after falling, it's just annoying.

This is being accompanied by some random triggers which play the same stock music whenever you walk past them, making you feel like you're watching some Bob Ross painting session.

Since everything is so barebones and barely functional, I'd say the guy who made the game is new to the dev scene and went for Unreal Engine for no proper reason because the game could have been great with any other, more accessible engine as well. The game is even using its template project name in the task manager so that says everything.

So as it is right now, the game is just not good. It looks great because of stock assets and unreal's lighting features but that's really it. The gameplay is average, it lacks some features and the poorly implemented voice lines and music are just tedious. Fix that and I'd actually enjoy the game.

생각보다 그레픽 리소스를 많이 잡아 먹기에 권장 사양에 나와있는 사양보다 더 높은 그레픽 카드를 권장합니다. 이로인하여 튕길시 세이브가 없다고 합니다. 즉 난이도가 기하급수적으로 늘어날 수 있습니다.
길찾기가 난해할때는 위를 보면 길이 보이고 그 길을 역순으로 따라 가면 거기가 길입니다.
난이도가 점프킹이나 포고스턱 항아리 보다 굉장히 낮은편이지만 태초마을로 떨어지면 피로도는 굉장히 오릅니다.
배경도 이쁘고 나름 재밋게 즐겼으며 돈값을 하는 좋은 게임입니다. 
직접해보는건 권하지는 않습니다.

Do you have depression, headaches, psychotic rage episodes, broken mouse, monitor, pc, desk, etc? If you don't, you will after playing this game! This game makes you want to punch a hole through your wall just because you fell off of a piece of cheese. DO NOT BUY THIS GAME IF YOU GET MAD EASILY AT GAMES!!! YOU WILL RAGE AT THIS GAME. The mechanics are super clunky for a game where you have to land near perfectly on everything. I have fallen countless times on things that doesn't make sense as to how I fell which leads me to question my existence and you are forced to hear the song that it plays while falling which leads you to want to strangle your own throat if you have to hear it more than once. I have never hated a game this much in my life and Call of Duty Modern Warefare 2- 2022 exists. Forget the rage you had with another game because this game will make you want to burn your house down because you fell from outer space right back to where you started because there is no saving in this game or checkpoints. I used to say 2k was the must rage inducing game but I couldn't have been more wrong. I have headaches after playing this game and it makes you want to cry if you fall from such a high place. Just when you think you are about to fall on something, the game says nope and then you slip off as if you just stepped on a banana peel. This is a terrible game and yes I wrote this after I fell near the end. Do not buy this game if you are a gentle being because it will turn you into a psycho and make you want to break everything in sight. After falling every single time I play this game, I have been granted the ability to only see red and I now believe that I can fully fight a rhinoceros 1 on 1 and win with ease. If you want to have a heart attack at an early age, play this game. If you want a new pc or monitor then play this game because there will be a fist in your monitor and you will throw you pc from an open window upstairs or you will just smash it with your bare hands like I probably will do here soon. May God bless you all and keep you with serenity and peace when playing this game, you will need it. 

-With eyes that see red,

After ALOT of time and persistence, I finally completed this game! It was quite the rough journey, with many ups, and many more downs. But making it all the way through, was thoroughly satisfying.

This game is best recommended for people with high tolerance levels because this game is akin to "Getting Over It with Bennett Foddy" in the sense that there is the chance you can lose all your progress in a single mistake.

People have complained about the absence of checkpoints and/or a save option. But quite frankly, those options would ruin the whole concept of the game and make it less of a challenge to players.
It's not meant to be a casual walk in the park, and the risk of losing progress by falling, or even by exiting the game is what makes this game so great. It pushes you to learn from your mistakes and discover new ways to eventually arrive at the end.

Rewarding. I was able to beat it with around 10 hours put in across 2 days most of which being getting a feel for the controls on day 1. My first play-through was just under 2 hours after watching speed runs for easiest skips.

Tips for beating:
1) DON'T RUN, for 90% of jumps running is not necessary and will make you overshoot, its better to undershoot and climb.
2) Set your camera perspective to straight instead of to the side by pressing 1. It helps with jumps.
3) Take shortcuts, beds are an easy way to skip difficult parts and are generally low risk.
4) Take breaks and don't give up, this sounds cringe but if you find yourself making less progress leave it for another day.

Once you beat it you'll realize it wasn't all too bad and you will be more compelled to speed-run the game.

DOG SHIT FUCKING GAME
Where do I even begin with the abomination that is Only Up? This game is a prime example of everything that's wrong with modern gaming. From its lackluster game play to its uninspired graphics, it fails to deliver even a modicum of entertainment. Only Up? More like Only Down, because that's exactly where this game will take your gaming experience.

Let's start with the game play, or should I say lack thereof? It's as if the developers took a checklist of all the cliches and tired mechanics in the industry and threw them into a blender. Repetitive jumping, mind-fumblingly simple puzzles, and a complete absence of any innovation make for a gaming experience that feels more like a chore than a form of entertainment. It's a shame that the game's title promises an ascent, because you'll be spiraling into boredom with every passing minute.

And don't get me started on the graphics. I've seen mobile games with better visuals than this so-called "next-gen" catastrophe. The characters look like they were designed by a kindergartner armed with a box of crayons. The environments lack any semblance of detail or creativity, leaving players with a bland and uninspiring world to explore. It's clear that the developers prioritized rushing this game out the door rather than putting any effort into making it visually appealing.

To add insult to injury, the sound design is equally disappointing. Forget about immersive audio or a memorable soundtrack; Only Up seems to have opted for a soundtrack that consists solely of a repetitive loop that grates on your nerves like nails on a chalkboard. It's as if they wanted to torture players and make them regret ever putting on their headphones.

But perhaps the most infuriating aspect of Only Up is the complete disregard for player enjoyment. The game is riddled with micro transactions and loot boxes, turning what could have been a mediocre experience into a blatant cash grab. It's clear that the developers care more about lining their pockets than delivering a satisfying gaming experience. Shame on them.

In conclusion, Only Up is a perfect example of how not to make a game. Its uninspired game play, lackluster graphics, and exploitative monetization strategies make it an absolute train wreck from start to finish. Save your time and money and stay far away from this abomination masquerading as a game. You'll thank me later.

非常に良いゲームだった。

この価格帯では、良い操作性と思われます。
途中慣性のバグなのか吹き飛ばされる事も多々ありましたが、自分の操作を改善しようと思える楽しさがプレイをさせてくれます。
また、スローモーを使う事で、比較的安全に登頂する事ができます。
細い足場や、長距離ジャンプによるショートカット等、早くクリアしたいという気持ちを抑えるか勇気を出すか、自分の一挙手一投足が反映されるゲームで、初見殺しもこのようなゲームには様式美として実装されています。

バグ関連
本作品はアンリアルエンジンを使用しているとのことで、どのような有名会社が使ってもバグは必ずでます。
当然の話ですが、理不尽なバグも確かに存在します。
プレイされている方はわかりますが、第一中間地点手前の建物にハマる場所が存在し、やり直しを余儀なくされます。
ただ、ゲーム自体のクラッシュに遭遇する事はありませんでした。

バグ１　スタート地点のサッカーボール
主人公が蹴ることによりボールが回転するのですが、その回転に巻き込まれ高速移動する事を確認しました。

バグ２　地形
地面に細い隙間が存在すると主人公の足が挟まりハマる事があります。
牢獄のように、四方が壁に囲まれ脱出不可能な場所も存在します。
また、本来行かないステージでの地形判定が雑だったりして、判定がなく落下するといった事もありました。

バグ３　主人公のつかみ判定
滑るように空中の足場につかみ判定が発生せず、落下する事があります。

ほかにもバグはありますが、代表的なのはこれらでしょう。

ゲームタイトルそのままに、ひたすら上空を目指すゲームです。
私はこういったゲームがとても苦手ですが、動画配信者に触発されてやってみることに。
もしかして自分にもできるかも？と思ってしまったのです。
……何度も何度も落下を経験し続けると、だんだんとキャラクターのできること・できないことを理解します。
また同時に、プレイヤーとしてやっていいこと・やってはいけないことを理解します。
最初のうちはたったの数時間でクリアする上手なプレイヤーやRTA走者の真似をしてはいけません。
遠回りの確実な道を往き、着々とスキルを磨きましょう。
自分なりの安全な道を知り、注意すべきオブジェクトを覚え、跳ばずに掴まるという選択肢を手に入れ、歩いているとき・駆け足のとき・ダッシュしているとき……
それぞれのジャンプ力を見極められるようになった頃、
過去にカタツムリが這うが如く歩んだ箇所は華麗なパルクールと共に一瞬で踏み越えることになります。
このゲームの実績達成者は2023年6月24日現在5%ほどですが、心が折れなければ絶対にクリアできるでしょう。
意外と操作にゆとりのある、けして難しいゲームではなかったからです……意地が悪くはありますが。
様々なショートカットを諦めた私のクリアタイムは43時間。震えるような凄まじい達成感でした。
素晴らしいアートが進む動機となります。高いところから眺める景観をぜひ堪能してください。
プレイヤースキルの成長を強く実感できるゲームとして、文句なくオススメです。
Пиздец, вы будете падать, но продолжите играть. Отнимает нервные клетки

挺有趣的游戏，我觉得它是强过“壶男”的，因为主角性能真的很强，手好像装了吸盘，还有时间暂缓的外挂。
我自认是一个大龄手残玩家，但是目前也已经通了两遍了，给还没通关的大家一些小TIPS，希望能帮到你：
①选择大于努力，一些好的路径规划能事半功倍。
②合理地使用shift冲刺，这游戏是有惯性的，这点很科学；但是shift能让你瞬间处于最大速度并远眺，这很不科学。
③双击Ctrl翻滚，如果你在空中使用则会垂直下落，这是你跳过头时的后悔药，在跑道跳电梯处和跳JK处格外好用。
④多用鼠标右键时间暂缓，这不丢人，我直到现在也会在跳油桶，跳黄卡车，跳书架的时候暂缓时间。
⑤画质调最低永远不会错，不要高估这游戏的优化和你电脑的性能。
⑥如果你超级回家了，不妨关上游戏明天再玩，我们大多数人并没有耻辱下播的压力。
⑦小心彩虹桥！

En tout cas, si vous avez un bon pc, que vous jouez en ZQSD et que vous aimez les jumps, ce jeu est fait pour vous.

This game, to me, has a good amount of difficulty, and I really didn't mind the controls. My only gripe is the inconsistency of where ledges are located in an object which makes it difficult to tell what jump gives you the highest chance of grabbing on.

Super janky and has lots of bugs, BUT this game is still good despite all of that. There's such a great idea for a challenging game here that even though the game is not good quality, I still thoroughly enjoyed it. I agree with a lot of people that there should be a way to save your game from where you left off. It can be difficult for a lot of people to commit 1.5-2 hours or more to sit down and complete this game in one sitting. If you fall, you fall, start over and try again. But if you have to stop playing for any other reason, it should not result in being forced to start over. Despite everything wrong with this game, I still recommend it and I had a blast playing it.

Only Up! is an addictive platformer where you start at ground level and climb up! The very casual and relaxing gameplay mixed with tense and anxiety inducing moments make for a unique and fun experience as you progress to the top. I found out about this game from speedrunning videos on Youtube and realized I had to give this a try. I’m so glad that I did. There were a few parts of the map that I had trouble platforming, but the challenge made me keep moving forward….or up! This was a super fun game that took me an afternoon to beat. As an achievement hunter, I’d love to see more achievements added for collecting items on your way up, for beating the game within a certain time, or beating the game multiple times! Any of those would be cool. Overall, I really loved my time with Only Up! and I look forward to future updates and possibly new content!

я наиграл 6 часов, вчера купил, прошел довольно далеко, до рая. Падал раз 5 вчера в самый низ, но сильно не горел стул, т.к. понимал, что падал только из-за простейших ошибок. 
Но дома выключили свет и я сделал рефаунд, потому что не кайф было заморачиваться. 

Но друзья подбили всё-таки допройти её и я купил заново :))
(почему-то после рафаунда пропали 2 часа, которые я наиграл вчера и показывает только опыт сегодняшний.) 

на самом деле не такая сложная игра. За 4 часа прошел полностью, падал в самый низ 3 раза. 
После того как поднимаешься выше аниме девочки, упасть в самый низ практически не реально. были несколько бесячих моментов, падал от динозавра, с дракона упал и в ледяной башне, где апельсин весит - улетел вниз в дырку, но чудом зацепился за пиксель текстуры. 

А больше прям сложных моментов не находил. Советую к прохождению однозначно, тем более людям с устойчивой психикой. 

Не слушайте хейт школьников и криворукх стримеров, игра не такая сложная, но интересная. Местами руки реально потели :)

2024年5月　追記

賛否が分かれるかもしれませんけど、
Only upの名前をパクった盗作などが多数出ている今、
このゲームは名作とは言えなくても、「しっかりとしたゲーム」だったと思います。
のちに出てくるゲームとも呼びたくないゴミパクリ作品なんかよりも、
何千倍もマシで、自分が作りたいものを作っていたゲームでした。

批判してしまい申し訳なかったです。
何だかんだ言って楽しませていただきましたし、
ゲーム制作者の方には感謝したいです。
今となっては…いいゲームだったよ。



当時のレビュー↓


まず全体的に理不尽です。失敗したときのリスクが大きいにも関わらず、
初見殺しや悪質な罠が複数あり、制作者の悪意を感じます。セーブやチェックポイントも無いので、
中断などもできず、何度も同じ個所を通らざるえなくなります。

さらに、自分はたどり着けませんでしたが、
ほぼノーヒントで、失敗すれば最初からやり直しの場所は、あまりにもどうかと思います。
動画サイトでの配信、投稿をされる方なら、誰かに感想を共有できるかもしれませんが、
それらを行わず、一人で楽しみたい方がプレイされた場合、苦痛は計り知れません。絶対にお勧めできません。
おまけにこの手のゲームにしては、お値段も1000円以上と高いです。

しかし上に登るというコンセプトは、アセット流用などがあったとしても好きです。
様々なものにジャンプして、上を目指していく、塔や山登りみたいな感じで、そんな雰囲気は好きです。
なんせ理不尽以外の、ゲームコンセプトは、正直気に入りまして、少年が高い所に掴みに行く、自分的にはロマンを感じます。

自分は、街付近で動けなくなり、返金しましたが、
セーブ機能やチェックポイント、巻き戻し機能などが追加された場合、また購入しようと思います。
恐らくそれらは望まれていない可能性が高いですが、私はユーザーフレンドリーな要素が追加されることを祈ります。

…のはずだったですが、なぜか再度購入してしまいました。不思議。

2023/06/26 追記

無事にクリアしました。達成感よりも、時間の無駄を痛感しました。
アセットの使い方はオシャレですが、相変わらず、低品質かつ理不尽なゲームです。
個人的に虹色の足場意外に、明らかに床の判定がない場所（雨が降る場所の屋根、迷路の一部など）に、
騙されて落ちるのも、都市部分の最後のタワーで、落ちる場所が悪いと進行不能になるのも辛いです。
とりあえずチェックポイントとセーブを追加してください。（最後のほうの救済の足場を他の所にも…。）
それを追加してくだされば、初見殺しやバグがあったとしても、ある程度評価できるゲームになると思います。
配信者及び動画投稿者の方は、映りが良いので、苦痛に耐えれるなら、購入は一理ありかとおもいます。
しかしそれ以外の方の購入は、現状絶対おすすめしません。

I did finish Only Up in a single day, took my 208 minutes to finish the game. This game is a rage baiter in order to get you mad over huge amounts of lost progress, and it doesn't have the cleanest platforming, but DOES have some pretty sick shortcut skips (if you want to risk huge amounts of progress if missed). I liked this game, but it ain't a good game.

Story/Characters
Don't fall, blah blah, random text generated lore. None of it makes sense apart from random quotes which range from telling me to give up, to saying may the force be with you at the very end. Also a ton of asset flips with surface level quotes so lol.

Gameplay
Rage inducing platforming, nothing new, and of course the controls are pretty jank. There are however pretty good mechanics in the game that I did like, which are the shortcuts in the game that give me a fun gut feeling as I skip through huge portions of the map, but at the risk of losing it all if I miss the shortcut and fall even further below. Other than that, you just jump across a bunch of asset flip platforms that just feel like the developer scrolled down free assets and just dragged a bunch of assets to create a platformer. It does have a ledge grab that makes the game a bit easier for precision jumping, but overall this game will just deflate you.

Music
huh? there is like 3 generic songs, and of course only one that stuck was the song that plays when you fall a shit ton just to rub it in.

Nitpicks/Last Positives
- So many falls were cause my character just slides off a platform or fails to ledge grab, which was infuriating.
- Slow motion did help for panic platforming
- a ton of "Twitter clip bait platforming where you lose HOURS worth of progress for simply not knowing", why?

Conclusion
This game was fun... when I finally finished the game. It isn't a good game, but I would be lying if I said I didn't enjoy my time with it and finally beating it. It is not the best rage inducing platform, but if you are looking for a 3d getting over it style where you just jump across a bunch of random assets, this gets it done, but play with a friend to prevent losing your mind while you go along the game.

Bought this and 1st tried it to the top in 75 minutes. Usually I like to equate $1 per hour of a game, but in this instance I felt so accomplished that I'm gonna let it slide.

PROS

• If you like jumping puzzles and butt clenching jumps then this game is for you 
• Graphics are good for the genre
• The game is fairly new but it seems like the devs are committed to adding, improving and fixing the game with promise of more to come.

CONS

• Jank physics. Just playing the game you'll know exactly what I'm talking about and in my run I ran into some bugs
• The game direly needs a save system. Currently if you want to complete the game you must do it all in one go because when you close the game, whatever progress you made is reset to the beginning of the game upon reopening the game. That being said, it's a time commitment.

Huge bug for me which toggles slow mo permanently for the rest of the run. When pausing or tabbing out of the game (which pauses the game) slow mo locks as activated and I have to hold the slow mo button to get back to normal speed, had to spend the entirety of my winning run holding RMB. Tried various window settings, resolutions, fps, vsync, issue persisted, so I had to make sure that over a multi-hour play session (since there are no saves or checkpoints) that I did not pause for any reason or need to use my computer for anything else, which does not work well for an overall boring game that I would like to take a break from or play a video or music during. I did not enjoy the platforming, and for a platformer that's the main thing which needs to feel good. The reliance on a mantle system made me feel like I spent the entire time catching myself on ledges instead of proper parkour fun. Even stairs and platforms that appeared to be walkable get stuck or pushed off unless you mantle up them. Regular walking and jumping feels like every object is circular, like a Weeble with vasoline on their shoes just slipping around but if you fall off a ledge you can just mantle back up... These elements come together to make easy platforming dotted with falls due to mechanical inconsistencies rather than player error, obviously it is the player inputting the commands but it feels like the success is based on something beyond the immediate control of the player, such as a mantle that just doesn't stick to terrain as expected, a jump that just doesn't take off even though there's floor below so the character just runs off the ledge, or after a big fall positioning yourself to land on a large flat platform just to slide off it and get sent even further back towards the favelas.

I liked the exploration available in the game that sometimes gives an alternate path besides the most obvious direction, and the world is enjoyable to look around. It is plain to see that someone had a lot more fun building an environment rather than making a good platform game. There are several shortcuts that feel like dev doors from someone who got tired of playing their own game and left them in, so it is possible to just skip many sections freely which feels like why even bother having that content in the first place if you know its boring and is more enjoyable to skip.

Technical issues that I hope will be fixed (today's update did not fix them) are the sound slider not working at all, and the slow mo being stuck on after attention is taken from the game window. There is no music or sound in most of the game besides some voice over and a few bars of music at certain points, so I wanted to play my own music but the slider for volume does not adjust anything, even setting the windows volume mixer does not change it either. When tabbing out to play music I came back to the game window and the slow mo controls were inverted, always on and right click returned to normal speed so I had to hold right click to play normally. This happened in windowed mode also, and the only solution was to quit to menu which does not save progress, even exiting the application restarts the entire game, so it is apparently expected to finish the game in a single sitting.

This game has nothing going for it besides the artsy setting and landscape which is cool to hang around in for a bit, and the only reason to play it is the zeitgeist online right now, once that fades in a few days don't bother.
Side effects include but are not limited to sweaty palms, anxiety, and increased risk of heart attack, highly recommend.

This game is worth $5 at most (probably more like $2.50). Took me about 4 hours to beat it. (Left the game on idle since there isn't a save option.) It's pretty janky and uses a lot of random assets from the unity store and other games. 

I think the reason why this game got so popular for streamers is because of the high-stakes game-play; it's really fun to watch streamers lose a ton of progress from one mistake. The level design itself is extremely random and abstract and the dialog is really odd. I love that you can take extremely risky shortcuts that can save a lot of time; I always tried to learn these shortcuts so whenever I fell, the trek back up was quicker.

Normally I would still give this game a thumbs up even with it's flaws, BUT the developer plastered his NFT all over the game as graffiti as well as graphics for your character model. So for this reason I don't recommend buying this game/ad for his nft.

An awful lot of jumps needs to be donde using wacky physics to progress, and sometimes taking a shortcut is more reliable and easier than the expected path.

Only Up plunges players into a bottomless pit of exasperation, where every fall erases all progress made. The developers of have clearly taken the phrase "failure is the key to success" to heart. With clunky controls and deceptive traps, it's a frustrating experience designed to question your life choices. The cheerful soundtrack mocks your failures, while the charming graphics hide a sadistic intent. Laughable in its absurdity, it traps you in an endless loop of falling and restarting.

한국게임이라고? 중국에 팔아먹은건 아니고?
메인화면 부터 한자에 중국풍이더니 한글 번역도 중국어를 구글번역기 돌려서 붙여넣기 한거같고
인게임에서 한국 관련된거는 시작할때 크고 시야가려서 아무도 안쓰는 쥐콩만한 태극기가 박힌 헬멧인데 이거보고 와 한국게임이었구나 했는데 신라면 컵라면 모양 하나 제외하면 전부 일본중국 냄새나는거 밖에 없음.
어차피 우리나라는 개성이없고 인지도도 일본 중국보다 부족해서 외국인들 입맛에 맞췄나보다 아니면 그냥 일본 중국이 좋아서 그런식으로 만들었구나 하고 생각했는데 드래곤 나오는부분에서 중국 국기가 거실에 걸린액자마냥 세로로 걸려있고 마치 보란듯이 나 중국게임이다 하면서 크기가 다른 국기들보다 3~4 배 큰거보고 정떨어져서 그냥 중국게임이구나 생각하기로했음.
발적화만 봐도 한국인이 만든게임은 확실함. 최적화 할 실력은없는데 무조건 그래픽만 따지는 딱 한국형 게임이긴한데
아마도 돈없어서 중국에서 투자받고 만들었던지 이름만 SC-KOREA 고 운영은 중국인들이 하는거일수도 있음.

인기를 얻은건 게임이 대단해서도아니고 방송용이라서임. 거지같은 캐릭터 움직임과 고르지못한 지형지물들 천지인데 그것들이 보는사람도 긴장하게 만들고 추락할때의 스트리머 반응때문이지 게임이 잘만들어져서 성공한게아님.
게임 점수는 딱 스팀평가가 정확함. 항아리 게임처럼 스킬베이스도 아니라서 일단 알고나면 난이도가 슈퍼마리오급으로 급락함.

외국사람들은 그냥 중국 게임으로 알고있고 태극기를 보고도 중국이라고 하는거보면 차라리 다행이다 싶음. 중국게임해라.

[h1]可远观不可亵玩[/h1]
这是一款看主播玩观赏性极强，自己玩了无生趣的硬核跑酷游戏。玩家扮演的贫民窟少年从地表爬上宇宙的历程既超现实又十分励志。相较于同样以不断攀升为目标的《蔚蓝》来说，玩家虽然在其中也能收获傲人的成就感，但是相应的挫败感怕也是成倍增长。游戏的优化相当拉胯，穿模现象不断，操作手感也不好，而且还不支持手柄。只建议纯高手和受虐狂亲自游玩，其余人群还是一起跟主播感受“欢声泪语”吧。

[h1]低血压看过来[/h1]
  虽然游戏很糙，但也不得不承认，这种天空布满未知领域、小伙子怎么都摔不死的离谱设定很酷。你可以把主角想象成是高空滚球游戏中的“球”。不过别想多了，这不是说你有多灵活，而是代表你有着随时都会失足的风险，且有过之而无不及。人家滚球掉落后还能到存档点重新开局，你人在万米高空一旦摔下来就得重走一遍八十一难取经路，心里没点强大的抗压能力真顶不住。
当然也有人说，每一次的更往上都能获得巨大的快乐。那我也只能说：这种快乐我不配！

 最后我想说机翻啥的我根本不Care，但麻烦加个官方手柄适配吧，这很难吗？

This game tries to copy the "Getting Over It with Bennett Foddy" experience and fails miserably. I gave the game a good try, I really did, and I found myself leaving after about 20 minutes. It wasn't the game play itself that scared me away, but the quite terrible audio that really threw me for a loop.

The game imitates "Getting Over It" by following the difficult parkour interlaced with music and commentary, except that it simply gets every part wrong.

The music is bog-standard elevator music but has really strange cues that I can only assume are based on height level. For about one minute in my 20 minutes of playtime, I was stuck on a fence jumping over it repeatedly and triggering the same voice lines and music cues repeatedly, which completely destroyed any appreciation I actually had for it.

I have to assume that the voice lines aren't recorded and are in fact AI generated because they sound absolutely terrible.  There just isn't any emotion to be found in the voice lines, which is such a shame for a game that seems to be attempting to tell a really deep and personal story on the narrator's behalf. I just couldn't appreciate the narration because I felt like I was listening to my Amazon Alexa tell me about it's trauma while I just couldn't be bothered. Finally, I stopped playing after 20 minutes because at no point did I feel that the game was really difficult. This game holds your hand by auto-catching yourself on the nearest ledge meaning all you have to do is walk sideways and fall backwards on any straightaway and you'll never fall off. In addition, the game treats itself to really tedious obstacles; forcing you to run across train tracks and pipes for 70% of the "Parkour", essentially just functioning as a walking simulator. The existence of slow-motion just adds on to my theory that the purpose of this game was to cash in on the popularity of Bennett Foddy's own parkour game.

I just can't recommend it on any grounds; real disappointment.

"Only Up!" is an exceptional game that delivers an unparalleled gaming experience. Developed by a talented team of designers, programmers, and artists, this game has captivated players worldwide with its innovative mechanics, stunning visuals, and addictive gameplay.

One of the standout features of "Only Up!" is its unique concept. Unlike traditional games where the objective is to navigate through different levels horizontally or in various directions, "Only Up!" focuses solely on vertical movement. Players are tasked with guiding their character upward through a series of challenging obstacles, platforms, and puzzles.

The gameplay mechanics in "Only Up!" are smooth, responsive, and intuitive. Controlling the character's ascent is a joy, thanks to the precise touch controls or seamless integration with motion-sensing technology. Whether you're playing on a mobile device or a gaming console, the controls are optimized for each platform, ensuring a seamless and enjoyable experience.

Visually, "Only Up!" is a treat for the eyes. The game boasts stunning graphics, vibrant colors, and meticulously designed environments. Each level is a visual feast, featuring imaginative and beautifully crafted worlds that players can explore as they ascend. From lush jungles and towering skyscrapers to mystical realms and futuristic cities, the game's visual variety is awe-inspiring.

The level design in "Only Up!" is where the game truly shines. Each level is meticulously crafted, presenting unique challenges, puzzles, and surprises at every turn. From timing jumps between moving platforms to solving intricate puzzles to progress, players will find themselves engaged and constantly pushing their skills to the limit.

To enhance the replay value, "Only Up!" offers a range of customization options. Players can unlock and choose from a wide selection of characters, each with its own unique abilities and playstyle. Additionally, the game features a comprehensive progression system that rewards players with achievements, upgrades, and unlockable content as they conquer more levels and challenges.

Furthermore, "Only Up!" offers a robust multiplayer mode, allowing players to compete with friends or players from around the world. Whether it's racing to the top or engaging in cooperative gameplay to overcome difficult obstacles together, the multiplayer mode adds an extra layer of excitement and social interaction to the game.

In conclusion, "Only Up!" is a stellar game that sets new standards in the gaming industry. With its innovative vertical gameplay, stunning visuals, challenging level design, and engaging multiplayer mode, it provides an immersive and unforgettable gaming experience. Whether you're a casual gamer or a seasoned pro, "Only Up!" will undoubtedly leave you hooked and craving for more vertical adventures.

Sweaty Palms: The Videogame

Jokes aside, I actually found this game pretty fun. Maybe I'm weird.

I like the idea of this game but the bad controls, janky camera, and general glitchiness reduce it from being a frustrating but fun and eventually satisfying game like Getting Over It to being a truly torturous experience. 

Here's a quick example to illustrate the difference between this and a frustrating but fun game like Getting Over It. At one point I was riding a cart on a railway in a part of the game that isn't supposed to be challenging, it is just supposed to give you a chance to look down at the favelas while the narrator speak. Half way through I turned the camera to look below me and I glitched off the cart and through the rails below me, landing back at the start of the game. Keep in mind I never even had my fingers on the move keys, I was simply moving the camera and looking around as you are supposed to do at that part of the game.

Maybe the dev can fix issues like this in time, but I can't see myself giving it another chance.

игра полная хуета, так как за малейшую ошибку еблана разработчика который создал игру для компов наса и не догадался сделать адекватного взаимодействия модельки персонажа со всем остальным говном на карте. рекомендовать этот кусок сырого поноса в таком состоянии просто нахуй нельзя. Бегите блять как можно дальше от этой игры. платить за это безумие просто 500 рублей овер дохуя. тем более если есть геттинг овер ит где разработчик создавал игру, а не хуйню в которой ты будешь страдать просто так из-за лени и глупости идиотов в команде разрабов. Игра по задумке и идеи охуенная, в плане механики могла быть очень хорошой, но к сожалению ее делали пидорасы. Так что рекомендация всем людям на планете нахуй, дождитесь когда игру доделают и в нее будет нормально играть, дождитесь нормальной оптимизации и 90 процентной скидки, тогда эта игра будет хороша, сейчас же лучше смотрите ее у стримеров или просто забейте на нее хуй лет на 5, как раз когда вспомните игра будет выглядите как должна быть, еще и скидки будут.

p.s я прошел эту хуйню, но из-за бага игры мне пришлось потратить на 6 часов больше, так как почти в самом конце я застрял в текстурах из которых не выбраться и мне пришлось начинать все заново, благо в этот раз получилось без багов, но так же с глупыми падениями по вине игры из-за которых страдал я. Так что мой совет остается таким же, не покупайте этот кусок сырого поноса за 500 рублей. Дождитесь скидок, мой вам настоятельный совет.

p.s все что сейчас произошло подтверждает мои слова что игра полное говно

I got the game because I like challenging games. To be fair the concept of the game is fun and catched my interested from the very first beginning.
But for me as a variety gamer I play lots of different games and I see red flaggs whenever there are some.
The graphics are OKish. But the reason for me to refund after a playtime of 80 minutes was defenetly the object collision code. Dont get me wrong. I like a hard game BUT I got bounced off countless times. Got stuck in visible and also invisible walls. Which made me fall again of course. Having not a single save point or checkpoint is ok for me. But I had to restart my PC due to windows problems. I couldnt save my progress and restart were I needed to quit the game. Thats an absolute NO-Go for me.
So overall a nice concept but not well developed. Bugs. awfull object collision coding and yes some people mentioned the TTS and the poor "story telling" for me not worth playing and the first refunded game for a veeeeeerry long time.

9시간만에 클리어했습니다. 이런 류의 게임은 클리어의 쾌감을 목적으로 진행을 하기 때문에,  조작감이 다소 불편하더라도 감안하기 마련인데, 솔직히 부류치고 조작감은 나이스한 편입니다. 대부분 초반 조작방식, 조작감 때문에 초반에 헤메이기 마련인데, 이 게임을 하시는 분들 90%이상은 이에 대한 불편함은 솔직히 거의 없었을꺼라고 봅니다. 세이브가 없다는것에는 이 게임의 아쉬운점으로 꼽을꺼 같은데, 개인적으로는, 세이브가 없기 때문에 조금 더 스릴있고 집중해서 했던거 같습니다. 침대, 트램펄린등 일정 구간을 쉽게 스킵할 수 있는 기믹들을 찾는 재미가 더 배가 된 이유가 여기에 있다고 보기 때문입니다. 하지만 일부 자잘한 버그나, 모르면 태초로 가야만 하는 기믹들은 큰 아쉬움과 감점요소인 것 같네요. 특히 모르면 떨어져야지? 하는 부분의 경우, 절대 무시할 수 없는 높이에서 직행하는 부분이기 때문에, 그 게이머가 1시간을 했건 10시간을 했건간에 절망을 줘버릴 수 밖에 없기 때문이죠, 본인의 실수가 아닌 낚시로 인해 손해를 보는건 게이머의 인성에 영향을 미치기때문에,... ㅋㅋㅋ  아무튼 항아리류 같은 똥겜중에선 가격대비 나쁘지 않은 게임이였습니다. 개인적으로는 8.2/10 점 정도인 것 같습니다.

Das Spiel ist ähnlich zu einem anderen Spiel nämlich AltF4, auf welches ich mich auch beziehen werde als Beispiel, da es die meisten bereits kennen, um das Spiel in einen Wort zu beschreiben würde ich Interessant sagen, aber mehr gibts unten.

Schwierigkeit:
In AltF4 gab es mehr "zufällige Dinge" die passiert sind wie z.B. Fische,Kanone oder Schweine die in dich rein geflogen sind, es gab also einerseits Einfluss vom Spieler aber auch vom Spiel. In diesem Spiel hast du wenn überhaupt Plattformen die runter fallen wenn du drauf springst, heißt nach dem ersten mal weißt du wo welche "Fallen" sind. Abgesehen davon sind die beiden übrigen Gründe, weswegen man runter fallen könnte, die folgenden: entweder ist man zu gierig und springt vorbei ("skill issue") oder der Charakter meint sich nicht an eine Kante ranzuhängen.

Negativ:
Und da kommen wir auch zum Hauptpunkt weswegen das Spiel mich negativ stimmt. Es kann nicht sein, dass das Spiel Erlebnis behindert wird, durch Bugs und es passiert nicht nur ein,zwei mal sondern sehr oft das der Char sich nicht an eine Kante eines Objektes dranhängt, obwohl man hoch genug ist und die Hitbox offensichtlicher weise berührt. Allgemein sind Hitboxen eher hingeklatscht obwohl sie das Spiel ausmachen. So sind die Schachfiguren, Treppen und weitere Stellen so komisch, dass der Char runterrutscht. Wäre dieser Makel nicht da, (wobei ich mir auch vorstellen könnte das es extra ist) könnte man nur noch an skill issue scheitern und das Spiel wäre um einiges einfacher als AltF4.

Positiv:
Das Spiel bietet eine schöne und entspannte Musik zwischendurch. Die Musik die kommt wenn man runterfällt würde ich auch eher als amüsant bezeichnen im Zusammenhang mit der Synchronsprecherin obwohl die schon echt nervig ist, da sie extra provokant sein soll und ich daher eher als lustig auffasse. Das Spiel hat super Passagen und zur eigentlich jeder Passage von der Synchronsprecherin einen kleinen Text. Ich konnte noch nicht alles entziffern aber ich bin mir sicher das sich eine kleine Geschichte dahinter verbirgt. Nun zum Hauptpunkt es ist mal wieder ein gutes JnR bis auf oberiges genannt, weil einfach der Zusammenklang stimmt und wie die meisten JnR ob aus MC oder AltF4 kratzt es am Ego wenn man so ein eigtl. einfaches Spiel nicht schafft, wodurch einen die Sucht direkt packen kann. 

Ich kann es aufjedenfall weiter empfehlen, nicht nur weil ich persönlich auf Spiele mit Schwierigkeit und Herausforderung stehe und somit die "Challenge" schaffen will, sondern auch da die Atmosphäre einfach stimmt.

If you're looking for a review on this game you've come to the wrong place, but if you're looking for an outstanding pie recipe you've come to the right place.

Ingredients:

1. 6 tablespoons unsalted butter
2. 1/2 cup white sugar
3. 1/2 cup brown sugar
4. 1/4 cup water
5. 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon
6. 1 pinch salt
7. 5 apples - peeled, cored and sliced
8. 1 pastry for double-crust pie

Directions:

1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).
2. Combine butter, white sugar, brown sugar, water, cinnamon, and salt in a saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, remove from heat and set aside.
3. Roll out half the pastry to fit a 9-inch pie plate. Place bottom crust in pie plate; pour in apple slices.
4. Roll out top crust into a 10-inch circle. Cut into 8 (1-inch) wide strips with a sharp paring knife or pastry wheel. Weave the pastry strips, one at a time, into a lattice pattern. Fold the ends of the lattice strips under the edge of the bottom crust and crimp to seal.
5. Pour butter-sugar mixture over top of pie, coating the lattice, and allowing any remaining sauce to drizzle through the crust.
6. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C), and bake until the crust is golden brown, the caramel on the top crust is set, and the apple filling is bubbling, 35 to 40 more minutes. Allow to cool completely before slicing.

Она напоминает мне наш жизненный путь. И воодушевляет меня идти дальше, и я вижу в ней глубокий смысл.

Маленький мальчик идет к своей цели где-то там наверху и путь его далеко не легкий, но все равно он идет в верх несмотря на падения и трудности. Это игра напоминает мне наш жизненный путь! Как бы мы не хотели у нас в жизни всегда будут падения и подемы, но мы просто не имеем права сдаваться ради своих целей и желаний! Даже если очень хочется.

Я так много раз падал в жизни, что хотелось плакать! От меня уходили друзья и предавали те кому я доверял самое сокровенное в своей жизни. Я много раз думал бросить все! И все равно некогда не бросал ведь если я сдамся то докажу всем что я слабак и самое главное докажу себе что я мусор, который не смог пройти этот путь! Поэтому я никогда не сдамся. Так и в этой игре, после падения как бы низко ты не упал ты ОБЯЗАН ВСТАТЬ! И пойти дальше ведь в конце пути тебя ждет та самая мечта!

This entire game is made for shilling out NFTs. The clothes your character wears, the art on all the walls, it's all Goblintown NFT shilling. *There is one or more NFTs on screen at all times.*

Edit: I have since also learned that a large chunk of the assets in this game were stolen from other games, and even some solo 3D artists. 

This game was made for the sole purpose of passively advertising NFTs through unknowing streamers; This is the only game this developer has ever put out, and it's a lazy asset flip with TTS narration, packed with stolen work, all so that they could fill it to the brim with Goblin Town NFTs and logos. Not a great look for their one and only release, and not something I will be supporting after learning this.

Overall, interesting concept with much more work to be done to earn a recommendation. There are differences between game mechanics being complex, difficult, and broken. The major pro to Only Up! is that it offers a great range of difficult and complex puzzles to navigate. What ultimately does in my recommendation is the broken grab and camera mechanics. Sometimes the player grabs onto obstacles even when you think it wont. Other times, during critical obstacles or jumps, the grab mechanic just 'breaks' and the animation fails to work correctly. Thus, 20-30+ minutes can be ruined; not by player error but straight up the game not working correctly. Until this critical piece is fixed, no one should be paying for this game.

Начиная играть в эту игру я вспомнил отрывки из клипа песни "Red Hot Chili Peppers - Californication".
Там ребята также бегали, менялась локация и выглядит все довольно воодушевленно.
Есть моменты, которые определенно стоит доработать в игре. Первую часть багов пофиксили, но с новым патчем добавились новые баги. Проваливаешься под карту, застреваешь в текстуре или персонаж дважды подряд хватается за одно и тоже место.
В целом скажу, что игра хорошая и не каждый сможет ее пройти. 
Очень красивые локации, которые будут после первого тайм-зачета.
Бегать по таким локациям одно удовольствие!
Между ног у девушки мурчит киска, прыгаешь по разным фруктам, шоколадным батончикам, презервативам, а так же по различным бытовым предметам.

○雑に強力なスローモーション能力と、そこそこ吸い込める崖掴まり能力で登っていく3Dプラットフォームアクション。
やることは狭い足場を跳んで歩いて登るだけだけど、色んなオブジェがあって景色が変わるのは飽きなくて良いかも。
ワンミスで数十分戻されるので気をつけよう。

✗ただ、床が見た目より実際の判定が小さくてジャンプ踏み切りがし辛かったり、床抜けバグがあったり、オブジェクトの間に挟まって詰みになったりと、作りの甘い部分は多々ある。
また、冒頭の以外にも全くプレイヤーに責任のない初見殺しでがんばりを台無しにしてやろうという歪んだ思想を随所に感じる。
難ゲーって、ゲームとプレイヤー間に「成功に対して報酬、失敗に対してペナルティ」という約束があって成立するものだと思ってるけど、これはそういう信頼を裏切ってくるタイプ。
アプデ紹介文で「賭け金の上昇とリスクを楽しんでほしい」とか言ってたけど、テーブルをそっちの気分でいつひっくり返されるか分かんない状態で賭け事をどう楽しむのかな。

あと、セーブもコンティニューもないから（実装予定も思想上ない）から、まとまった時間がないと一生クリアできないと思う。

数時間プレイしちゃったから返金もできないし、やった時間を無駄にしたくないからクリアまではやろうかなと思うけど、その間楽しいのか、その後に達成感が得られるかはわかんないな。
With the right amount of discipline, anything is possible.

跌落判定超鬼, 有毫無提示的初見殺. 捷徑重要度遠大於正常路徑顯得正常路線很弱能
第一二部分的花樣和失敗路線比第345部分都多. 第5部分易到靠北. 愈往上走花樣就愈少
最後一部分就突顯一個懶字. 只是跳台連環跳就穩過. 還有大平台給你保底.第二部分又不見你那麼好心. 

但優點就是長度夠而且不算難,而且有暴力級的場地分割,有很多點你會省時間從而愈跳愈好. 會練跳床又會無聊玩玩的話就能體會自己愈玩愈快的成長感. 你想對自己有挑戰性就能在這遊戲找回一點樂趣

總結就3d平台高畫質跳跳遊戲看上去有喙頭,本質還是個爛遊戲.關卡設計愈復愈懶. 想受苦可玩.正常人不建議

アプデ後に初めてプレイした感想です。
アプデ前がどうだったかはわかりませんが、色々改善されてプレイしやすくなった（らしい）です。
良い点
・操作感に違和感などがない。（アプデで良くなったらしい）
・踏み外しても復帰できる。
・ショートカットできる場所が沢山ある。
・オブジェクトの量が多くてグラフィックが良い。
・その割にバグが少ない。（私は致命的バグにあっていない）
・スローが使える。
悪い点
・使用許可を得ているのかわからないようなBGM。
・スタート地点にあたかもクリア報酬かのような宇宙服のヘルメットがある。
・ショートカットが沢山あるゆえの難易度。（簡単すぎる）
まとめると
パパっとプレイできて登山ゲームをそんなにやったことない人にでもオススメできるような簡単なゲームです。
初見殺しがたまにしかなく、周りを見渡せば次に登るべき場所がだいたい把握でき、ちょっと踏み外しても主人公の腕力で助かることがあり、さらにスローまで使える。
なんて優しいゲームなんだ！！
プレイヤーが増えたことで賛否両論出てきて、その意見を聞いてちゃんとアプデをいれて調整している時点で良い運営！
今後の新しいモードとできれば新しい実績が増えることに期待しています。

I like the game, even though it screams "lazy" all over and has a ton of bugs. I just like going up I guess. 
However, I can't recommend this game currently because there is no progression saving. So when playing an hour of going up, and then for whatever reason needing to take a break and exiting the game, you lose all your progress. This for me is a no go. I can't have a game that requires me to put in set amount of hours to beat the game in one sitting only because otherwise i lose all that i have gained. That is insanity. I don't mind losing progress due to falling back down by my own mistakes, but when a simple break from the game becomes a full reset, that is where i draw the line.

So until a update comes where progression saving is added, i am refunding the game.

很好玩的游戏，不理解为什么评价不好，差评集中在bug多脚滑没存档点上，然后恼羞成怒喷，说得好像脚不滑了你就能过了一样。 那些给差评的但凡看到后面关卡昂首独立的guoqi，应该也会打个好评，可惜这些人应该是看不见，八成是心血来潮试了试然后在管道上哆哆嗦嗦还掉下去被搞得气急败坏就跑了。游戏设计只能用美来形容，不管是景象还是bgm都可谓优美艺术，不断向上的方向给了人们昂扬的心，通关过程还能磨砺出足够刚强的意志，速通老实人多条路线更是让速通党满意风景党也满意。客观来说跳跃的综合难度是够高的，没有存档点掉落重来的设计是令人恼火的。但只要你坚持一下你会发现你的手法越来越纯熟，通关后会获得极大的满足感，觉得难就给差评脚滑就崩溃的我觉得是过于情绪化的，这游戏早期开发者道路还没关的时候有些地方确实恶心管道都要跳两次否则就会掉下去，有些地点甚至会直接卡死。相比之下altf4设计比较好有间隔性的存档点2里甚至有相当多的便利道具，但现在bug修的七七八八都差不多了作者是一直在优化的，综合来说游戏值得自己一试，如果你急于通关看看攻略速通其实不难，静下心来看看路上的风景你会发现这个游戏真的很美。
